Negative binomial regression
Y_i \sim \text{Poisson}(\lambda_i) and \lambda_i \sim \text{Gamma}(\mu_i, \psi)
E(Y_i) = \mu_i and \text{Var}(Y_i) = \mu_i + \psi \mu_i^2
P(Y_i = y_i) = \frac{\Gamma(y_i + k)}{\Gamma(y_i + 1) \Gamma(k)} \left(\frac{\mu_i}{\mu_i + k}\right)^{y_i} \left(\frac{k}{\mu_i + k}\right)^{k}
Above is the same as Y_i \sim \text{Negative Binomial}(\mu_i, k) where k = \frac{1}{\psi}
If \psi = 0 then Negative Binomial reduces to Poisson.
